[b]Market Exhaustion[/b] fuses Money Flow Index and Stochastic RSI into a single exhaustion panel, extended with higher-timeframe context, JMA smoothing, and regular divergence detection.

[b]What it does[/b]

Exhaustion signals emerge when momentum indicators reach extremes while price is still pushing in the same direction — a divergence between what price is doing and what the underlying flow is doing. This indicator combines two complementary exhaustion measures (MFI for volume-weighted flow, StochRSI for momentum velocity) and checks them against a higher timeframe to filter out noise from counter-trend conditions.

[b]Features[/b]

[list]
[*][b]MFI + StochRSI fusion[/b] — Both indicators evaluated together; signal requires agreement
[*][b]JMA smoothing[/b] — Optional Jurik smoothing on both series for cleaner signals
[*][b]Adaptive MFI zones[/b] — Dynamic overbought/oversold levels with optional background highlights
[*][b]Auto-HTF MFI context[/b] — Higher-timeframe MFI read displayed as a bias label
[*][b]Divergence detection[/b] — Regular divergences on MFI flagged directly on the panel
[/list]

